              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "CRC32 is used as a hash function. CRC32 is not a cryptographic hash — it\nis designed for error detection, not security. It is trivially reversible and\nvulnerable to collision attacks. Use SHA-256 or SHA-3 for cryptographic purposes.\n"
