              "name": "resources.rules.go.pg-orm-sqli",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Opengrep Finding: resources.rules.go.pg-orm-sqli"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Detected string concatenation with a non-literal variable in a go-pg ORM\nSQL statement. This could lead to SQL injection if the variable is user-controlled\nand not properly sanitized. In order to prevent SQL injection,\ndo not use strings concatenated with user-controlled input.\nInstead, use parameterized statements.\n"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "enabled": true,
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Detected string concatenation with a non-literal variable in a go-pg ORM\nSQL statement. This could lead to SQL injection if the variable is user-controlled\nand not properly sanitized. In order to prevent SQL injection,\ndo not use strings concatenated with user-controlled input.\nInstead, use parameterized statements.\n",
                "markdown": "Detected string concatenation with a non-literal variable in a go-pg ORM\nSQL statement. This could lead to SQL injection if the variable is user-controlled\nand not properly sanitized. In order to prevent SQL injection,\ndo not use strings concatenated with user-controlled input.\nInstead, use parameterized statements.\n\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [https://pg.uptrace.dev/queries/](https://pg.uptrace.dev/queries/)\n"
              },
              "properties": {
