                "text": "Opengrep Finding: resources.rules.go.go-inputval-unsafe-type-assertion"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Unsafe single-value type assertion in if-init statement. This will panic at runtime if the value does not hold the asserted type. Use the two-value form: if val, ok := $VAR.($TYPE); ok { ... } and check ok before using val.\n"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "enabled": true,
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Unsafe single-value type assertion in if-init statement. This will panic at runtime if the value does not hold the asserted type. Use the two-value form: if val, ok := $VAR.($TYPE); ok { ... } and check ok before using val.\n",
                "markdown": "Unsafe single-value type assertion in if-init statement. This will panic at runtime if the value does not hold the asserted type. Use the two-value form: if val, ok := $VAR.($TYPE); ok { ... } and check ok before using val.\n\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [https://go.dev/tour/methods/15](https://go.dev/tour/methods/15)\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
