            {
              "id": "dd639427-6799-3ae0-b128-5d54d2bc1de6",
              "name": "resources.rules.go.go-sqli-string-concat-inline",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Opengrep Finding: resources.rules.go.go-sqli-string-concat-inline"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "SQL injection: a raw SQL query is built by directly concatenating a non-constant variable into a call to a database query function (Raw, Query, Exec, Where). If any argument is derived from user input an attacker can inject arbitrary SQL. Use parameterized queries with ? placeholders and pass user values as separate arguments; never build SQL strings with string concatenation or fmt.Sprintf.\n"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "enabled": true,
                "level": "error"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "SQL injection: a raw SQL query is built by directly concatenating a non-constant variable into a call to a database query function (Raw, Query, Exec, Where). If any argument is derived from user input an attacker can inject arbitrary SQL. Use parameterized queries with ? placeholders and pass user values as separate arguments; never build SQL strings with string concatenation or fmt.Sprintf.\n",
                "markdown": "SQL injection: a raw SQL query is built by directly concatenating a non-constant variable into a call to a database query function (Raw, Query, Exec, Where). If any argument is derived from user input an attacker can inject arbitrary SQL. Use parameterized queries with ? placeholders and pass user values as separate arguments; never build SQL strings with string concatenation or fmt.Sprintf.\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-89",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/89.html"
                  }
                ],
